# AI-Powered ER Triage System — Implementation Plan

A full-stack emergency room triage assistant. A nurse clicks **Record**, speaks patient details in natural language, and the system uses AI (Gemini API) to extract structured data and place the patient on a live priority Kanban board.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Gemini API Key**: The backend calls the Gemini API. You will need to provide your Google Gemini API key. It will be placed in the Spring Boot `application.properties` as `gemini.api.key=YOUR_KEY_HERE`. Please have it ready before running the backend.

> [!NOTE]
> **Stack Summary**:
> - Frontend: React 18 + Vite
> - Backend: Java 17 + Spring Boot 3 (REST, JPA, H2)
> - AI: Google Gemini 1.5 Flash API (via HTTP)
> - Voice: Web Speech API (browser-native, zero cost)
> - Database: H2 In-Memory

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend — Spring Boot

#### [NEW] `d:\demo\er-triage-backend\` (Maven project)

**Files to create:**
- `pom.xml` — Spring Boot Web, H2, Spring Data JPA, Lombok, Jackson
- `src/main/resources/application.properties` — H2 config, CORS, Gemini key placeholder
- `Patient.java` — JPA entity: id, name, age, symptoms, vitals, priority (RED/YELLOW/GREEN), rawInput, timestamp
- `PatientRepository.java` — `JpaRepository<Patient, Long>`
- `GeminiService.java` — Calls Gemini REST API with a strict system prompt to extract JSON `{age, symptoms, vitals, priority}` from raw speech text
- `PatientService.java` — Orchestrates: receives raw text → calls GeminiService → maps to Patient entity → saves → returns DTO
- `PatientController.java` — REST endpoints:
  - `POST /api/patients` — body: `{rawInput: string}`, returns saved patient card JSON
  - `GET /api/patients` — returns all patients sorted by priority + timestamp
  - `DELETE /api/patients/{id}` — remove a patient card
- `CorsConfig.java` — Allow requests from `http://localhost:5173`

---

### Frontend — React + Vite

#### [NEW] `d:\demo\er-triage-frontend\` (Vite project)

**Files to create:**
- `src/App.jsx` — Root, sets up layout (Header + KanbanBoard + VoiceInput)
- `src/api/patientApi.js` — `fetch`-based API calls to Spring Boot
- `src/components/Header.jsx` — Branded top bar with title and status indicator
- `src/components/VoiceCapture.jsx` — Web Speech API recording button, status display, transcript preview, submits to backend
- `src/components/KanbanBoard.jsx` — 3-column layout (Critical/Red, Urgent/Yellow, Standard/Green), polls `GET /api/patients` every 3 seconds
- `src/components/PatientCard.jsx` — Card showing name, age, symptoms, vitals, timestamp, dismiss button
- `src/index.css` — Full design system: dark navy theme, glassmorphism, gradient accents, animations

